div.p:
The versified selections are as follows: Ruskin’s book 1 begins with the latter half of Scott’s chap. 5, 
                        the Sacristan’s failure to gain passage over the drawbridge and, in fording the Tweed on horseback, his encounter with the White Lady; 
                        and book 1 ends by briefly summarizing portions of Scott’s chap. 7, the Abbot and Father Eustace’s resolve on hearing the Sacristan’s adventure.
